<!--
Hardened Runtime entitlements for the notarized anima CLI (Phase 3G G2.2).

By default, Hardened Runtime denies:
  - attaching a debugger
  - loading unsigned dylibs
  - JIT allocation
  - dyld interposition

That baseline is exactly what we want. We do NOT opt in to any relaxations —
the anima CLI spawns child processes (osascript, zenity, PowerShell for the
vault-agent confirmation prompt in Phase 3F), which does NOT require any
entitlement beyond the default sandbox-free + hardened-runtime set.

Do NOT add:
  - com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory (enables JIT; huge
    attack surface, no use case for a static Bun binary)
  - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation (would allow loading
    unsigned dylibs; breaks the trust chain that makes notarization worth
    anything)
  - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables (weakens the
    runtime against DYLD_* injection attacks)

If a future feature breaks under Hardened Runtime, prefer fixing the feature
over adding an entitlement. A regressed trust model is worse than a missing
feature.
-->
